== NzbDAV Backend Architecture Rules ==

**Core Technology Stack**

- Framework & Tools

- .NET 9 - Latest .NET runtime and framework
- ASP.NET Core - Web framework with built-in DI container
- Entity Framework Core - ORM with SQLite database
- NWebDav.Server - WebDAV protocol implementation
- Serilog - Structured logging framework
- FFMpegCore - Media file processing
- SharpCompress - Archive handling (RAR/ZIP)
- Usenet library - Usenet protocol client

Project Structure

- Single executable project (OutputType: Exe)
- Nullable reference types enabled
- Implicit usings enabled
- Target Framework: net9.0
- File Structure & Organization

Directory Architecture

Api/
├── Controllers/ # REST API endpoints
│ ├── BaseApiController.cs # Base controller with auth
│ ├── BaseApiResponse.cs # Standard response format
│ └── FeatureName/ # Feature-specific controllers
│ ├── FeatureController.cs
│ ├── FeatureRequest.cs
│ └── FeatureResponse.cs
├── SabControllers/ # SABnzbd-compatible API
Clients/ # External service clients
├── Connections/ # Connection pooling utilities
Config/ # Configuration management
Database/ # Entity Framework context & models
├── Models/ # Entity models
├── Migrations/ # EF Core migrations
├── Interceptors/ # Database interceptors
Exceptions/ # Custom exception types
Extensions/ # Extension methods
Middlewares/ # ASP.NET Core middleware
Queue/ # Background processing
├── FileProcessors/ # File type processors
├── FileAggregators/ # File collection logic
├── DeobfuscationSteps/ # File name deobfuscation
Streams/ # Custom stream implementations
Tasks/ # Background services
Utils/ # Utility classes
WebDav/ # WebDAV implementation
├── Base/ # WebDAV base classes
├── Requests/ # WebDAV request handlers
Websocket/ # WebSocket management

Naming Conventions

- Namespaces: PascalCase following folder structure - NzbWebDAV.Api.Controllers
- Classes: PascalCase - MediaIntegrityService
- Files: PascalCase matching class name - MediaIntegrityService.cs
- Interfaces: IPascalCase - INntpClient
- Enums: PascalCase - ItemType
- Constants: PascalCase - IdPrefixLength

**Dependency Injection & Service Lifetimes**

Service Registration Patterns

- Singleton: Stateful services, managers, configurations
  builder.Services.AddSingleton<ConfigManager>();
  builder.Services.AddSingleton<WebsocketManager>();
  builder.Services.AddSingleton<UsenetStreamingClient>();
- Scoped: Database contexts, request-scoped services
  builder.Services.AddScoped<DavDatabaseContext>();
  builder.Services.AddScoped<DavDatabaseClient>();

Constructor Injection

- Use primary constructors: public class Service(Dependency dep)
- Inject interfaces when available: INntpClient not NntpClient
- Avoid service locator pattern

**Database Architecture**

Entity Framework Patterns

- Database-First approach: Models reflect database schema
- Migration-based: Use EF Core migrations for schema changes
- SQLite database: Single file at /config/db.sqlite
- Connection per request: Scoped DavDatabaseContext

Model Conventions

- Primary keys: Use Guid for entities with public IDs
- Navigation properties: Include [JsonIgnore] for serialization
- Required properties: Use = null! pattern for EF Core
- Static instances: Define well-known entities as static readonly

Database Access

- Repository pattern: Use DavDatabaseClient wrapper
- Async operations: Always use async methods with CancellationToken
- Using statements: Always dispose contexts: await using var context

**API Controller Architecture**

Base Controller Pattern
[ApiController]
[Route("api/feature-name")]
public class FeatureController(Dependencies deps) : BaseApiController
{
protected override async Task<IActionResult> HandleRequest()
{
// Implementation
}
}

Request/Response Pattern

- Each endpoint gets: Controller.cs, Request.cs, Response.cs
- Request parsing: Use new FeatureRequest(HttpContext)
- Response format: Inherit from BaseApiResponse
- Error handling: Automatic via BaseApiController

Authentication & Authorization

- API Key authentication: Via FRONTEND_BACKEND_API_KEY environment variable
- WebDAV basic auth: Username/password from configuration
- Override auth requirement: Set RequiresAuthentication = false

**WebSocket Architecture**

Topic-Based Messaging

public static readonly WebsocketTopic TopicName = new("short", TopicType.State);

Topic Types

- State topics: Send current state on connect + updates
- Event topics: Only send new events, no state persistence
- Message Broadcasting
  \_ = websocketManager.SendMessage(WebsocketTopic.TopicName, "message");

WebSocket Client Lifecycle

- Authentication required: API key on connection
- Auto-reconnection: Handled by frontend WebSocket client
- State persistence: State topics automatically send last message

**Background Services & Tasks**

Hosted Service Pattern

- Inherit from: Background service or implement IHostedService
- Singleton lifetime: Register as singleton
- Cancellation support: Use CancellationToken throughout
- Error handling: Catch exceptions, log, and continue

Queue Processing

- Producer/Consumer: Use QueueManager for work items
- File processors: Implement specific file type handlers
- Debouncing: Use DebounceUtil for progress updates

**Configuration Management**

ConfigManager Pattern

- Centralized configuration: All config through ConfigManager
- Database-backed: Config stored in ConfigItems table
- Type-safe getters: Create specific methods for each config
- Event notifications: Subscribe to OnConfigChanged

Configuration Methods

public bool IsFeatureEnabled()
{
return GetConfigValue("feature.enabled")?.ToLowerInvariant() == "true";
}

public int GetFeatureTimeout()
{
if (int.TryParse(GetConfigValue("feature.timeout"), out var timeout))
return Math.Max(1, timeout);
return 30; // Default value
}

**Logging Patterns**

Serilog Configuration

- Structured logging: Use named parameters in log messages
- Log levels: Configure via LOG_LEVEL environment variable
- Console output: ANSI color theme for development

Logging Best Practices

- Log.Information("Processing file {FilePath} for user {UserId}", filePath, userId);
- Log.Warning("Failed to process {FilePath}: {ErrorMessage}", filePath, ex.Message);
- Log.Error(ex, "Unexpected error processing {FilePath}", filePath);

Performance Logging

- Use LogEventLevel.Debug for detailed tracing
- Use LogEventLevel.Information for business events
- Use LogEventLevel.Warning for recoverable errors
- Use LogEventLevel.Error for exceptions

**Stream & File Processing**

Custom Stream Classes

- Purpose-built streams: Inherit from Stream for specific use cases
- Disposal pattern: Implement IDisposable properly
- Async operations: Support ReadAsync, WriteAsync with cancellation
- Buffering: Consider memory usage for large files

File Processing Pipeline

- File Detection: Determine file type (NZB, RAR, media)
- Validation: Check file integrity and completeness
- Processing: Extract, decompress, or stream content
- Cleanup: Dispose resources and temporary files

**Error Handling & Exceptions**

Custom Exception Types

- Domain-specific: Create exceptions for business logic errors
- Inheritance: Inherit from appropriate base exceptions
- Serializable: Support serialization for distributed scenarios

Exception Middleware

- Global handler: ExceptionMiddleware catches unhandled exceptions
- Response format: Convert to standard JSON error responses
- Logging: Log exceptions with full context

Error Recovery

- Retry logic: Use exponential backoff for transient failures
- Circuit breaker: Implement for external service calls
- Graceful degradation: Continue operation when possible

**Extension Methods**

Extension Patterns

- Static classes: Use static classes for extension methods
- Namespace alignment: Match namespace with extended type
- Null checking: Check for null in extension methods
- Performance: Avoid allocations in hot paths

Common Extensions

public static class StringExtensions
{
public static bool IsAny(this string value, params string[] acceptedValues)
{
return acceptedValues.Any(acceptedValue => value == acceptedValue);
}
}

**External Client Integration**

HTTP Client Pattern

- Base client class: Common functionality in ArrClient
- Derived clients: RadarrClient, SonarrClient with specific logic
- Connection management: Use HttpClient with proper disposal
- Retry policies: Implement retry for transient failures

Usenet Client Architecture

- Connection pooling: Manage multiple NNTP connections
- Thread safety: Use thread-safe wrappers
- Caching: Cache frequently accessed data
- Authentication: Handle credentials securely

**Performance Considerations**

Memory Management

- Dispose pattern: Always dispose database contexts and streams
- Async operations: Use async/await throughout
- Cancellation: Support cancellation tokens in long operations
- Streaming: Process large files as streams, not in memory

Caching Strategies

- In-memory caching: For configuration and frequently accessed data
- Connection pooling: Reuse expensive connections
- Lazy loading: Load data only when needed

Database Optimization

- Query optimization: Use appropriate indexes and queries
- Batch operations: Process multiple items together
- Connection management: Use scoped contexts appropriately

**Security Patterns**

Authentication

- API keys: Use environment variables for secrets
- Password hashing: Use secure hashing with salt
- Session management: Implement proper session timeout

Authorization

- Role-based: Check permissions in controllers
- Resource access: Validate user access to specific resources
- API security: Validate all inputs and sanitize outputs

**Testing Considerations**

Testability Patterns

- Dependency injection: Makes unit testing easier
- Interface segregation: Create testable abstractions
- Pure functions: Separate business logic from side effects

Integration Testing

- Database testing: Use in-memory or test databases
- External services: Mock HTTP clients and external dependencies
- End-to-end: Test complete workflows

**Deployment & Environment**

Environment Variables

- CONFIG_PATH: Configuration and database location (/config)
- LOG_LEVEL: Logging verbosity (Debug, Information, Warning, Error)
- FRONTEND_BACKEND_API_KEY: API authentication key
- MAX_REQUEST_BODY_SIZE: Maximum request size in bytes

Container Considerations

- Health checks: Implement /health endpoint
- Signal handling: Graceful shutdown via SIGTERM
- File permissions: Handle Docker volume permissions
- Process isolation: Single responsibility per container
